Dan Uggla’s Hitting Streak Ends at 33 Games in Braves’ 6-5 Loss to Cubs

-- B y   L a r r y   S i d d o n s
-- 
2011-08-15T01:00:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-15/dan-uggla-s-hitting-streak-ends-at-33-games-in-braves-6-5-loss-to-cubs.html
Dan Uggla’s hitting streak ended at
33 games when he went 0-for-3 as his  Atlanta Braves  lost to the
Chicago Cubs 6-5.  Uggla’s streak tied for 19th in Major League Baseball
history, according to baseball-almanac.com. The record is 56
games by  Joe DiMaggio  of the  New York Yankees  in 1941.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Siddons at 
 lsiddons@bloomberg.net  